Manila Electric, Petron, San Miguel: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-06-02T01:04:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/manila-electric-petron-san-miguel-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 1 percent to
4,286.46.  Manila Electric Co. (MER)  : The largest Philippine power
retailer is in talks with potential partners for its venture
into power generation, a stock exchange filing showed. The
company plans to build a portfolio of up to 1,500 megawatts of
power projects and invest 9 billion pesos ($209 million) in
equity for an initial 600 megawatts of generating capacity, it
said. The stock gained 4.1 percent to 250 pesos.  Petron Corp. (PCOR)  : The largest Philippine oil refiner
was rated new “buy” with a 12-month share price target of
17.50 pesos by Jody Santiago, an analyst at UBS AG. The stock
gained 0.6 percent to 13.48 pesos.  San Miguel Corp. (SMC)  : The largest Philippine food and
drinks company was rated “outperform” in new coverage at
Credit Suisse Group AG. The brokerage has a share-price estimate
of 135 pesos, analysts led by Dante Tinga wrote in a report. The
stock climbed 2.9 percent to 114 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
